lied Mathematics Major  servesas the President of the VMI Honor Court  and is a captain of the VMI baseballteam   See accompanying article for more on Cadet Geary  16   This Parent s Weekend banquet tradition has become the most important annual eventfor the Keydet Club  It is so encouraging to bring together all of ourscholarship cadet athletes and many of the generous donors and FundRepresentatives  who make their educations possible  said Keydet Club CEO GregCavallaro  84   Allowing our cadet athletes an opportunity to interact with VMI benefactors and to be inspired  challenged and motivated by outstanding guest speakers  gives them aglimpse of what their futures could hold  As meaningful as the dinner is for our cadet athletes  it is also encouraging to hear from so many of those who generously support VMI athletics as to how inspired they are after having spent such a meaningful and engagingevening with their cadet athlete and parents  concluded Cavallaro  Wes Foster  56 had this to say about the event   We were very impressed with theKeydet Club s Scholarship Awards Banquet  It was so nice to meet thecadets on our scholarships and see how much it means to their parents  Iwas only able to attend VMI and walk on to the Football Team because of 3 or 4alumni scholarships   so I know the impact and the lifelong opportunitiesattending VMI gave me  The entire evening was outstanding  just wonderful Betty and I should have been coming every year  We will from now on  Following remarks on the state of VMI athletics and a warm introduction by VMI s 14thSuperintendent  General J H  Binford Peay III  62  this year s guest speaker Mr  Gerald J  Acuff  Jr   71  did not disappoint with his inspirational andmoving remarks that culminated with a rousing standing ovation   The scholarship banquet  as always  affirms the dedication of the VMI communitythat annually steps up to support the education of our cadet athletes Our cadet athletes  coaches and the entire department are sincerely gratefulfor not only the scholarship support  but for the warm relationships that existbetween our scholarship donors and those that benefit from their support remarked Dr  David Diles  Athletic Director  For more information on next year s banquet or how to join in the effort to supportVMI s cadet athletes  please contact the Keydet Club at 800 444 1839  or visitthe Keydet Club s web site at www vmi edu keydetclub  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI   OUR MISSION  To contribute to the Spirit and development of a successful Division I Athletic Program  that benefits the WHOLE OF VMI  THE VMI KEYDET CLUB Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839    P  540 464 7328    F  540 463 2695  2014 VMI   Lexington  Virginia 24450 Privacy Policy   Webmaster 